SIMPLE: postgraduate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Postgraduate
<hw>Post*grad"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>post-</ets> + <ets>graduate</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or designating, the studies pursued after graduation, esp., after
receiving the bachelor's degree at a college; graduate.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A student who pursues such
studies.</def></def2></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Most careful writers consider the word
<xex>graduate</xex> to be the proper word to use in this
sense.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Posthaste</ent>⟦br⟧
